===Verb===
{{en-verb|fulminat}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive|figuratively}} To make a [[verbal]] [[attack]].
# {{lb|en|transitive|figuratively}} To issue as a [[denunciation]].
#* De Quincey
#*: They '''fulminated''' the most hostile of all decrees.
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[thunder]] or make a loud noise.
# {{lb|en|transitive|now|_|rare}} To strike with [[lightning]]; to cause to [[explode]].
#* '''2009''', Thomas Pynchon, ''Inherent Vice'', Vintage 2010, p. 235:
#*: the present owners couldn't afford the electric bills anymore, several amateur gaffers, sad to say, having already been '''fulminated''' trying to bootleg power in off the municipal lines.

